Ask HN: How about we rename FAANG to MAMAA?
text: I still hear people refer to the top tech companies as FAANG, but I think that term is outdated because Netflix is waning in relevance and two of the FAANG companies have changed their names. So, I propose that we switch from saying "FAANG" to "MAMAA" (Meta, Apple, Microsoft, Amazon, Alphabet). I also think this acronym is more fun to say (example: referring to big tech as "big MAMAA") and maybe even a metaphor for how smaller companies are like children beholden to MAMAA's platforms. Anyone with me?
